<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="299" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[130,775,1246,1350]" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">
DIAGNOSIS. — Aedeagal shaft with three spine-shaped straight processes subapically on right side and one spine-shaped straight subapical process on left side and with two short and two long spine-shaped slightly curved processes below on right and left sides (
<figureCitation box="[663,764,1325,1350]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="9.[132,143,998,1016]" captionTargetBox="[132,1457,224,1061]" captionTargetId="figure-502@9.[132,1455,214,1019]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIG. 5. — Limentinus perineti (Evans, 1953) n. comb., ZIN: A, first and second metatarsomeres, ventral view; B, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; C, pygofer lobe, inner side; D, subgenital plate, lateral view; E, aedeagus and connective, ventral view; F, same, lateral view; G, apex of aedeagus, lateral view; H, style, lateral view; I, connective, dorsal view. Abbreviations: al, additional lobe; vl, ventral lobe. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947025" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Fig. 5E, F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="300" pageId="4" pageNumber="299" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[132,439,1396,1485]" box="[132,277,1396,1422]" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[132,439,1396,1485]" box="[132,226,1427,1453]" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">
<emphasis box="[132,226,1427,1453]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Structure</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[132,439,1396,1485]" box="[132,439,1459,1485]" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">As mentioned for the genus.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[130,777,1523,2028]" box="[132,357,1523,1549]" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">
<emphasis box="[132,357,1523,1549]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">
Coloration (
<figureCitation box="[256,319,1523,1549]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[132,143,1069,1087]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,214,1026]" captionTargetId="figure-471@4.[132,1455,208,1026]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG. 1. — Limentinus perineti (Evans, 1953) n. comb., holotype, MNHN-EH-EH2701: A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, frontal view; D, labels. Total length of the specimen: 7.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947011" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947011/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Figs 1</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[334,348,1523,1549]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="5.[178,189,1207,1225]" captionTargetBox="[132,1442,215,1163]" captionTargetId="figure-324@5.[132,1455,152,1163]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIG. 2. — Limentinus perineti (Evans, 1953) n. comb., male, ZIN: A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, frontal view. Total length of the specimen: 7.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947015" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947015/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">2</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[130,777,1523,2028]" lastBlockId="4.[811,1457,1172,1421]" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">
Face yellow, with two wide black stripes running from ocelli throughout frontoclypeus and fused in one stripe on anteclypeus (
<figureCitation box="[194,281,1618,1644]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[132,143,1069,1087]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,214,1026]" captionTargetId="figure-471@4.[132,1455,208,1026]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG. 1. — Limentinus perineti (Evans, 1953) n. comb., holotype, MNHN-EH-EH2701: A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, frontal view; D, labels. Total length of the specimen: 7.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947011" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947011/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Figs 1C</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[292,329,1618,1644]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="5.[178,189,1207,1225]" captionTargetBox="[132,1442,215,1163]" captionTargetId="figure-324@5.[132,1455,152,1163]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIG. 2. — Limentinus perineti (Evans, 1953) n. comb., male, ZIN: A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, frontal view. Total length of the specimen: 7.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947015" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947015/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">2C</figureCitation>
); apical enlarged part of anteclypeus with brown yellow margins; lorae black, except brown yellow outer margins; genae with wide longitudinal black stripe under each eye running to level of lorae; antennae with scapus, pedicel, and flagellum light yellow; ocelli dark brown; rostrum brownish yellow. Crown black, except brown yellow lateral margins (
<figureCitation box="[312,400,1810,1836]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[132,143,1069,1087]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,214,1026]" captionTargetId="figure-471@4.[132,1455,208,1026]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG. 1. — Limentinus perineti (Evans, 1953) n. comb., holotype, MNHN-EH-EH2701: A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, frontal view; D, labels. Total length of the specimen: 7.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947011" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947011/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Figs 1A</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[414,451,1810,1836]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="5.[178,189,1207,1225]" captionTargetBox="[132,1442,215,1163]" captionTargetId="figure-324@5.[132,1455,152,1163]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIG. 2. — Limentinus perineti (Evans, 1953) n. comb., male, ZIN: A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, frontal view. Total length of the specimen: 7.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947015" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947015/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">2A</figureCitation>
). Pronotum and mesonotum black. Thorax below and coxae mainly black. Forewings dark brown to black, with black veins; corium with light brown yellow area along the costal margin almost from the basal cell to outer anteapical cell and with light brown yellow spot below the apex of clavus (
<bibRefCitation author="EVANS J. W." box="[403,529,1969,1996]" pageId="4" pageNumber="299" pagination="87 - 137" refId="ref7058" refString="EVANS J. W. 1953. - Les Cicadellidae de Madagascar (Homopteres). Memoires de l'Institut scientifique de Madagascar, Ser. E (Entomologie) 4: 87 - 137." type="journal article" year="1953">Evans 1953</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 44) (
<figureCitation box="[631,715,1969,1995]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="4.[132,143,1069,1087]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,214,1026]" captionTargetId="figure-471@4.[132,1455,208,1026]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIG. 1. — Limentinus perineti (Evans, 1953) n. comb., holotype, MNHN-EH-EH2701: A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, frontal view; D, labels. Total length of the specimen: 7.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947011" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947011/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Figs 1B</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[726,760,1969,1995]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="5.[178,189,1207,1225]" captionTargetBox="[132,1442,215,1163]" captionTargetId="figure-324@5.[132,1455,152,1163]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIG. 2. — Limentinus perineti (Evans, 1953) n. comb., male, ZIN: A, dorsal view; B, lateral view; C, frontal view. Total length of the specimen: 7.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947015" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947015/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">2B</figureCitation>
); apical cells with appendix brown cinereous. Fore and middle legs light yellow. Middle trochanters light yellow, with dark brown inner sides. Hind trochanters brown yellow. Hind femora dark brown to black in its basal 2/3 and light yellow in its apical third. Hind tibiae dark brown, with light setae. Hind tarsi brown yellow. Claws dark brown. Abdominal segments black, with light yellow hind margins. Genital block black, except light yellow lateral margin apically of subgenital plate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[811,1456,1459,2028]" box="[813,1048,1459,1485]" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">
<emphasis box="[813,1048,1459,1485]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[978,1041,1459,1485]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="9.[132,143,998,1016]" captionTargetBox="[132,1457,224,1061]" captionTargetId="figure-502@9.[132,1455,214,1019]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIG. 5. — Limentinus perineti (Evans, 1953) n. comb., ZIN: A, first and second metatarsomeres, ventral view; B, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; C, pygofer lobe, inner side; D, subgenital plate, lateral view; E, aedeagus and connective, ventral view; F, same, lateral view; G, apex of aedeagus, lateral view; H, style, lateral view; I, connective, dorsal view. Abbreviations: al, additional lobe; vl, ventral lobe. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947025" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[811,1456,1459,2028]" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">
Anal tube 1.5 times as long as wide, flattened ventrally. Anal column short. Pygofer lobe triangularly elongate, with an additional small lobe on apical angle under anal tube and with ventral lobe in its middle (
<figureCitation box="[1106,1191,1586,1613]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="9.[132,143,998,1016]" captionTargetBox="[132,1457,224,1061]" captionTargetId="figure-502@9.[132,1455,214,1019]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIG. 5. — Limentinus perineti (Evans, 1953) n. comb., ZIN: A, first and second metatarsomeres, ventral view; B, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; C, pygofer lobe, inner side; D, subgenital plate, lateral view; E, aedeagus and connective, ventral view; F, same, lateral view; G, apex of aedeagus, lateral view; H, style, lateral view; I, connective, dorsal view. Abbreviations: al, additional lobe; vl, ventral lobe. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947025" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
); apical lobe with seven macrosetae subapically on its inner side (
<figureCitation box="[1242,1325,1618,1645]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="9.[132,143,998,1016]" captionTargetBox="[132,1457,224,1061]" captionTargetId="figure-502@9.[132,1455,214,1019]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIG. 5. — Limentinus perineti (Evans, 1953) n. comb., ZIN: A, first and second metatarsomeres, ventral view; B, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; C, pygofer lobe, inner side; D, subgenital plate, lateral view; E, aedeagus and connective, ventral view; F, same, lateral view; G, apex of aedeagus, lateral view; H, style, lateral view; I, connective, dorsal view. Abbreviations: al, additional lobe; vl, ventral lobe. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947025" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate long and narrow, not narrowing apically, with microsetae apically and with long setae on main surface, including several subapical macrosetae (
<figureCitation box="[1088,1177,1714,1741]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="9.[132,143,998,1016]" captionTargetBox="[132,1457,224,1061]" captionTargetId="figure-502@9.[132,1455,214,1019]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIG. 5. — Limentinus perineti (Evans, 1953) n. comb., ZIN: A, first and second metatarsomeres, ventral view; B, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; C, pygofer lobe, inner side; D, subgenital plate, lateral view; E, aedeagus and connective, ventral view; F, same, lateral view; G, apex of aedeagus, lateral view; H, style, lateral view; I, connective, dorsal view. Abbreviations: al, additional lobe; vl, ventral lobe. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947025" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus asymmetrical, shaft long and narrow, slightly curved, with small hook apically bearing marginal denticles (
<figureCitation box="[1164,1226,1778,1805]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="9.[132,143,998,1016]" captionTargetBox="[132,1457,224,1061]" captionTargetId="figure-502@9.[132,1455,214,1019]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIG. 5. — Limentinus perineti (Evans, 1953) n. comb., ZIN: A, first and second metatarsomeres, ventral view; B, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; C, pygofer lobe, inner side; D, subgenital plate, lateral view; E, aedeagus and connective, ventral view; F, same, lateral view; G, apex of aedeagus, lateral view; H, style, lateral view; I, connective, dorsal view. Abbreviations: al, additional lobe; vl, ventral lobe. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947025" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
E-G), with three (2 + 1) spine-shaped straight processes subapically on right side and one spine-shaped straight subapical process on left side and with two short and two long (one is damaged) spineshaped slightly curved processes below on right and left sides respectively (
<figureCitation box="[948,1055,1937,1964]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="9.[132,143,998,1016]" captionTargetBox="[132,1457,224,1061]" captionTargetId="figure-502@9.[132,1455,214,1019]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIG. 5. — Limentinus perineti (Evans, 1953) n. comb., ZIN: A, first and second metatarsomeres, ventral view; B, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; C, pygofer lobe, inner side; D, subgenital plate, lateral view; E, aedeagus and connective, ventral view; F, same, lateral view; G, apex of aedeagus, lateral view; H, style, lateral view; I, connective, dorsal view. Abbreviations: al, additional lobe; vl, ventral lobe. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947025" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Fig. 5E, F</figureCitation>
); gonopore probably subapical. Styles elongate, narrowing apically, with rounded apices (
<figureCitation box="[1353,1441,1969,1996]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="9.[132,143,998,1016]" captionTargetBox="[132,1457,224,1061]" captionTargetId="figure-502@9.[132,1455,214,1019]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIG. 5. — Limentinus perineti (Evans, 1953) n. comb., ZIN: A, first and second metatarsomeres, ventral view; B, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; C, pygofer lobe, inner side; D, subgenital plate, lateral view; E, aedeagus and connective, ventral view; F, same, lateral view; G, apex of aedeagus, lateral view; H, style, lateral view; I, connective, dorsal view. Abbreviations: al, additional lobe; vl, ventral lobe. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947025" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Fig. 5H</figureCitation>
). Connective arcuate (
<figureCitation box="[1035,1110,2001,2028]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="9.[132,143,998,1016]" captionTargetBox="[132,1457,224,1061]" captionTargetId="figure-502@9.[132,1455,214,1019]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIG. 5. — Limentinus perineti (Evans, 1953) n. comb., ZIN: A, first and second metatarsomeres, ventral view; B, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; C, pygofer lobe, inner side; D, subgenital plate, lateral view; E, aedeagus and connective, ventral view; F, same, lateral view; G, apex of aedeagus, lateral view; H, style, lateral view; I, connective, dorsal view. Abbreviations: al, additional lobe; vl, ventral lobe. Not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4947025" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4947025/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="299">Fig. 5I</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
